title: House sends key trade bill to Obama - CNNPolitics.com
text:
CNN.com
House sends key trade bill to Obama By Deirdre Walsh , CNN Senior Congressional Producer Updated 1749 GMT (0049 HKT) June 25, 2015 JUST WATCHED Key trade bill passes the Senate 01:12 Washington (CNN) Cementing a victory for President Barack Obama's trade agenda, the House of Representatives passed legislation on Thursday providing financial aid and training for those workers displaced by global trade. The trade adjustment assistance bill was approved 286-138, with the bulk of votes coming from House Democrats. The President is expected to sign that measure, along with a bill Congress already passed -- known as "trade promotion authority" -- giving him fast track authority to negotiate trade deals with global partners soon.
